cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.PF, cs.SE, cs.MS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with scalability analysis of numerical parallel applications.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance estimation of research applications through numerical simulations.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper presents a power fit model to estimate scalability and model throughput performance metrics.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the optimal use of system resources and the validation of the power fit approach for additional scientific applications.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is relevant as the paper deals with numerical simulations and the use of empirical constants in the power fit model.
